        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1243688144" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12602033915522508591">Sadly I did not really like this book much. It began well with some nice descriptions of the Italian countryside and the chapters about the brother&apos;s life with the nuns were promising. However it then became a long sequence of silly coincidences and overly dramatic relationships and I found myself wishing it to be over. Possibly the worst part was the final section where we suddenly raced through a whole generation being born, growing up and getting married in the space of a few pages. Why? <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1943477.Kathryn_Stockett' title='Kathryn Stockett' rel='nofollow noopener'>Kath</a></span>
  <span id="freeText12602033915522508591" style="display:none">Sadly I did not really like this book much. It began well with some nice descriptions of the Italian countryside and the chapters about the brother's life with the nuns were promising. However it then became a long sequence of silly coincidences and overly dramatic relationships and I found myself wishing it to be over. Possibly the worst part was the final section where we suddenly raced through a whole generation being born, growing up and getting married in the space of a few pages. Why? <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1943477.Kathryn_Stockett" title="Kathryn Stockett" rel="nofollow noopener">Kathryn Stockett</a> is supposed to have described it as "a rich, sweeping epic." I did not find it rich, sweeping or epic, just another book which needed to be a lot shorter than it was.</span>
